40 is an excellent </div><div class="t mf1d x61 he yaf8 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">comment on verses 23-30. He who created the sea can speak </div><div class="t m1743 x64 he y91e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">peace to its troubled waters. But still more precious is the </div><div class="t m142c x64 he y16a7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">promise of peace to the troubled soul that calls upon Him. </div><div class="t m982 x64 he y90e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John 14: 27; 16: 33; Rom. 5: 1; Phil. 4: 6, 7. There is power </div><div class="t m1189 x64 he ya52 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in His word to perform that which He speaks. &quot;All His </div><div class="t ma53 x64 he y671 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">biddings are enablings.&quot; </div><div class="t mcea x66 he y2ee ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The last verse of the lesson makes clear the obligation to </div><div class="t m978 x61 he ya07 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">speak God&apos;s praise in the public congregation. Mal. 3: 16-18. </div><div class="t m756 x64 he y82d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This is especially enjoined upon those who see the end ap-</div><div class="t m18a x61 he y428 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">proaching. Heb. 10: 25. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
